  "explanation": [
    "안녕하세요 (annyeonghaseyo) is the most common polite greeting in Korean, used any time of day.",
    "Korean has different levels of politeness. 안녕하세요 is formal/polite, while 안녕 is casual and used with close friends.",
    "감사합니다 (gamsahamnida) is a polite way to say thank you. The more casual form is 고마워요 (gomawoyo).",
    "When saying goodbye, the phrase changes depending on who is leaving. Use 안녕히 가세요 to someone who is leaving, and 안녕히 계세요 when you are the one leaving."
  ]
